events.name: New York Knicks at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 25 points and five Charlotte players scored in double figures as the Hornets beat the New York Knicks 115-98 Thursday night for their fourth victory in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball scores 25 points, Hornets use balanced scoring to beat the Knicks 115-98

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored six of his 28 points in overtime and the Indiana Pacers defeated the Brooklyn Nets 105-99 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bennedict Mathurin scores 28 and leads Pacers to a 105-99 overtime victory over the Nets

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had 18 points, 11 rebounds and 12 assists for his second triple-double with Golden State, and the Warriors held on to beat the Toronto Raptors 117-114 on Thursday night after <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 18, but Curry injured in Warriors 117-114 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 35 points as the Chicago Bulls beat the Sacramento Kings 128-116 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 35 points to lead the Chicago Bulls to a 128-116 win over the Sacramento Kings

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 28 points and the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers 118-89 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo and Bucks pull away from short-handed Lakers for comfortable 118-89 win
